byline.contributor: Omar al-Jawoshy contributed reporting from Baghdad, and Iraqi employees of The New York Times from Tikrit and Basra.

abstract: Iraqi officials say that Libyan rebels found secret intelligence documents after the fall of Tripoli linking Col Muammar el-Qaddafi to a plot by former members of Saddam Hussein's military and Baath Party to overthrow the Iraqi government; Iraqi police have responded to the information by arresting more than 200 suspects in connection with the plot.
snippet: Col. Muammar el-Qaddafi may have been backing a Baathist-led coup against the Iraqi government.
